given to the value
investing community

00:48:36.910 --> 00:48:38.950
is the Value Investors Club.

00:48:38.950 --> 00:48:41.590
I'm sure most people here have
already visited the website.

00:48:41.590 --> 00:48:43.570
If you have not,
please check it out.

00:48:43.570 --> 00:48:45.190
It's an amazing resource.

00:48:45.190 --> 00:48:46.870
Joel, if you could
maybe just say

00:48:46.870 --> 00:48:50.770
a word about the Value
Investors Club, what's

00:48:50.770 --> 00:48:52.960
your vision with
it going forward?

00:48:52.960 --> 00:48:55.180
And how does it
compare or contrast it

00:48:55.180 --> 00:49:00.202
with other investing platforms
that are emerging these days?

00:49:00.202 --> 00:49:02.660
JOEL GREENBLATT: Sure, well,
it originally started in 1999.

00:49:02.660 --> 00:49:05.770
And the whole big
thing with the internet

00:49:05.770 --> 00:49:08.500
back then was getting
millions of eyeballs to look.

00:49:08.500 --> 00:49:12.190
And I viewed it more as
a, wow, I always wanted

00:49:12.190 --> 00:49:13.510
to be in an investment club.

00:49:13.510 --> 00:49:16.060
And I thought, hey, I could
form an investment club where

00:49:16.060 --> 00:49:17.860
you can meet any time,
at your convenience,

00:49:17.860 --> 00:49:21.610
wherever you are,
were, and share ideas

00:49:21.610 --> 00:49:23.410
and back and forth about it.

00:49:23.410 --> 00:49:26.950
And I'm always grading papers
at Columbia for my students.

00:49:26.950 --> 00:49:30.310
And at the time, there
were Yahoo message boards

00:49:30.310 --> 00:49:33.330
where 99.9% of the stuff
was not worth reading.

00:49:33.330 --> 00:49:39.925
So I sort of said,
hey, why don't we--

00:49:39.925 --> 00:49:41.300
along with my
partner John Petry,

00:49:41.300 --> 00:49:44.860
